3. Policy, Account Type, Linking Accounts and Account Security.
3.1  Registration Policy. To access the Services, or some of the resources they offer, You may be asked to provide certain registration details or other information. It is a condition of Your use of the Services that You (i) provide correct, current and complete information about Yourself as prompted by the registration form for the Services (such information being the "Registration Data") and (ii) maintain and promptly update the Registration Data to keep it correct, current and complete. You agree that all information You provide to register or otherwise, including without limitation through any interactive features of the Services, is governed by our Privacy Policy, and You consent to all actions we take with respect to Your information consistent with our Privacy Policy. You further agree that HER may provide any and all notices, statements, and other communications to You through email to the email address provided in the Registration Data.
3.2  Account Type.  There is no charge for creating an individual account ("Individual Account").  The Individual Account is for use by only the individual who opens the account for that individual's personal, non-commercial purposes.  In addition to Individual Accounts, HER provides licensed physicians and medical professionals working under the supervision of licensed physicians with the ability to purchase a professional account ("Professional Account").  The Professional Account is for use by the medical practice who purchases the License rights to it for the purpose of assisting in the treatment of patients whose Individual Accounts are linked to the Professional Account.  Please see our Fees & Payment Policy for information on the fees, payment provisions, term and additional termination rights for Professional Accounts.
3.3 Linking Accounts.  Individual Accounts may be linked to Professional Accounts, with the Individual Account owner's consent.  Please see our Consent for Individual Accounts Linked to Professional Accounts, which each Individual Account holder will be required to accept prior to linking of an Individual Account to a Professional Account.
3.4  Account Security.  If You create, or are provided with, a user name, password or any other information as part of our security procedures, You agree to treat such information as confidential, and that You will not disclose such information to any other person or entity. You further agree that Your account is personal to You and that You will not provide any other person access to the Services, or any portions of the same, using Your user name, password or other security information. You agree to notify us immediately of any unauthorized access to or use of Your user name or password or any other breach of security. You should use particular caution when accessing Your account from a public or shared computer or other device so that others are not able to view or record Your password or other personal information.
We have the right to disable any user name, password or other identifier, whether chosen by You or provided by us, at any time in our sole discretion for any or no reason, including if, in our opinion, You have violated any provision of these Terms of Use.
4. Links to Third Party Sites.
The Services may contain links to third party websites ("Linked Sites"). We do not control these Linked Sites and are not responsible for the content of, stability of, or any transmission to or from any Linked Site. HER provides these links to You only as a convenience and the inclusion of any link does not imply any endorsement by HER or any association with the Linked Site's operators, or guarantee that the content contains accurate information. We recommend You review the privacy policies and terms of use posted at any Linked Sites.
