* What security measures do we take to safeguard your personal information?
1. Application of our Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy applies to the use of our websites, www.skinsafeproducts.com (collectively, the "Site"), and our products, tools and services related to the Site (including without limitation our mobile and other software applications downloaded from the Site or obtained elsewhere, including our SkinSAFE mobile application) (collectively, the "Services"). This Privacy Policy does not apply to your use of any other apps or websites (including websites you access through the Site or Services or through an advertisement, service or content link). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of other apps or websites, and we encourage you to read each app's or website's privacy policy before providing any information. Also, this Privacy Policy only covers information collected through our Site or Services and does not cover any information collected by us through other means, including without limitation direct mail, paper applications and submitted forms.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand our policies and practices regarding collection and use of your information, and feel free to email us with any questions or comments at support@skinsafeproducts.com. By accessing or using the Site or Services, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
NOTICE REGARDING DISPUTE RESOLUTION:
Any disputes or claims arising under this Privacy Policy, or relating in any way to your use of the Site or Services, will be resolved by final and binding arbitration as provided for in our Terms of Use . Unless you opt out , you will only be able to pursue claims against SkinSAFE on an individual basis, not as part of any class or representative action or proceeding, and you will only be permitted to seek relief (including monetary, injunctive, and declaratory relief) on an individual basis.
2. Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. If we do, we will post the new privacy policy on this page and, if you are a registered user with an SkinSAFE account and have not opted out of receiving our emails, attempt to email you at the primary email address on your account. However, your continued use of the Site or Services after we make changes is deemed to be your acceptance of those changes, so please check this policy periodically for updates. The date that this Privacy Policy was last revised is identified at the top of the page.
3. Children Under the Age of 18 - Our Commitment to Children's Privacy
A special note to parents: The Site and Services are not intended for children under 18 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18. If we learn we have collected or received personal information from a child under 18 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that information. We also recommend that parents monitor their children's Internet activities and learn and employ software or other tools which can help their children enjoy the fun and entertainment of an on-line experience without compromising their personal safety or allowing them to use the Internet in a manner inconsistent with their parents' preferences. If you believe we might have any information from or about a child under 18, please contact us at support@skinsafeproducts.com.
4. Information We Collect and How We Use It
We may collect from you, or you may provide to us, both personal and non-personal information, which we may use to (i) provide you with the Site and Services and their contents, and any other information, products or services that you request from us, (ii) customize the content and advertising you see through the Site or Services, (iii) improve the services we provide to you, (iv) give you notices about your account and when updates are available and (v) carry out our obligations and enforce our rights arising from any contracts entered into between you and us, including for billing and collection.
We have designed certain portions of the Site and Services so that you can view them as a visitor without providing SkinSAFE with any Personal Information or creating an SkinSAFE account. However, certain portions of and activities on the Site and Services may require you to create an SkinSAFE account and become a registered user, including contributing to or commenting on discussion boards and forums, asking or answering health-related questions, sharing health-related information, tips or stories, creating a user profile, or sharing content from the Site or Services via email, SMS or MMS.
We collect information from and about users of our Site and Services: (i) directly from you when you provide it to us; and (ii) automatically when you use the Site or Services.
Information You Provide to Us
When you create an account on the Site or Services, we may ask you to provide personally identifiable information, including a username, email address, birthday, ZIP code, Age, City, State, Country, personal interests, gender, photographs and any other information we might collect that is defined as personal or personally identifiable information under applicable law (collectively, "Personal Information"). This information also may include (i) information you provide by filling out forms on the Site and Service when you register, enter contests and promotions, or report a problem with the Site or Services, (ii) records and copies of correspondence (including SMS, MMS and email messages and phone numbers), if you contact us, (iii) your responses to surveys, (iv) details on transactions you carry out through the Site or Services, or (v) your search queries on the Site or Services. You also may publish or display information on public areas of the Site, Services or related websites ("User Contributions"). As discussed further below, your User Contributions are posted and transmitted to others at your own risk, and we cannot control the actions of third parties with whom you share your User Contributions nor guarantee your User Contributions will not be viewed by unauthorized persons.
Information Collected Automatically and Tracking
We may collect certain aggregate and non-personally identifiable information in the normal course of operating the Site and Services that does not reveal the specific identity of any individual or relate to a single identifiable user.
When you download, access or use the Site or Services, we may automatically collect: (i) device information including your IP address, operating system, hardware ID, mobile network information, and browser type and language, (ii) usage details including access times, traffic data, location data, communication data, resources accessed through the Site and Services and referring website addresses, (iii) stored information including meta data and other information stored on your device, and (iv) location information including real-time information about the location of your device. We also may collect information about your activities over time and across third-party websites, apps or other online services (behavioral tracking). For information related to opting out of certain types of tracking see "Advertising" below. If you do not want us to collect this information, please edit your "Profile Information" to review your information collection options.
We may use information we collect about your location to provide you with more relevant advertising or direct you to nearby experts and service providers that may be able to answer your health-related questions or assist with your health-related needs. However, you must opt-in for us to use your location.
Information Collection Technologies
We use technologies for automatic collection of aggregate and non-personal information. These technologies may include "Cookies", web beacons or other website technology. Cookies are pieces of information sent to and stored on the computer or device you use to access or use the Site or Services. We use cookies to collect anonymous information about your use and help us generate customized content, monitor traffic on our Site and Services, and track entries to our sweepstakes. We do not store any identifying information in any cookies on your computer. Your browser software can be set to reject all cookies or to accept cookies only from our Site or Services. Most browsers offer instructions on how to reset the browser to reject cookies in the "Help" section of the toolbar. However, if you reject our cookies, you may not be able to log in or use certain functions and conveniences of our Site or Services.
